xplained. The introduction describes examples of Lie equations and known integrability theorems, and gives applications of the theory to be developed in the following chapters and in the subsequent volume.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aDifferential equations. 0aLie algebras. 0aLie groups. 7aMATHEMATICS / Algebra / Linear.2bisacsh  aAdjoint representation.  aAdjoint.  aAffine transformation.  aAlexander Grothendieck.  aAnalytic function.  aAssociative algebra.  aAtlas (topology).  aAutomorphism.  aBernhard Riemann.  aBig O notation.  aBundle map.  aCategory of topological spaces.  aCauchy–Riemann equations.  aCoefficient.  aCommutative diagram.  aCommutator.  aComplex conjugate.  aComplex group.  aComplex manifold.  aComputation.  aConformal map.  aContinuous function.  aCoordinate system.  aCorollary.  aCotangent bundle.  aCurvature tensor.  aDeformation theory.  aDerivative.  aDiagonal.  aDiffeomorphism.  aDifferentiable function.  aDifferential form.  aDifferential operator.  aDifferential structure.  aDirect proof.  aDirect sum.  aEllipse.  aEndomorphism.  aEquation.  aExact sequence.  aExactness.  aExistential quantification.  aExponential function.  aExponential map (Riemannian geometry).  aExterior derivative.  aFiber bundle.  aFibration.  aFrame bundle.  aFrobenius theorem (differential topology).  aFrobenius theorem (real division algebras).  aGroup isomorphism.  aGroupoid.  aHolomorphic function.  aHomeomorphism.  aInteger.  aJ-invariant.  aJacobian matrix and determinant.  aJet bundle.  aLinear combination.  aLinear map.  aManifold.  aMaximal ideal.  aModel category.  aMorphism.  aNonlinear system.  aOpen set.  aParameter.  aPartial derivative.  aPartial differentia